5:
Far to the west of Palpebra lies a
country blessed with fertile land and
the water of a great river.
8:
It is known as the Farlandsâ€”ruled by
a king and the Nine Noble Houses.
10:
Its relations with Palpebra have
always been tense, but in recent
years a fledgling peace was built
between them.
16:
However... That peace did not come
easily.
23:
Individuals stood by their pride, and
groups stood by their interests.
These shadows long loomed over
the path which was to lead to light.
26:
We were likely no exception. Those
shadows blinded us too...
31:
Once upon a time, there lived a man
known as the Swallow Knight.
33:
Yuwel Nouin, born to the ninth of the
Noble Houses. His valor was
unquestionable.
35:
When the kingdom was swarmed by
monsters and its people required
aid, he alone rose to the occasion.
36:
He formed the Swallow Knightsâ€”true
warriors who fought for the people.
And their loyalty to this cause, in
turn, filled the people with hope.
38:
They fought and fought, striding
toward the light. No matter the
struggle or defeat...
41:
I pray that I, too, may one day reach
that light.
47:
There you are! Wake up, Yuwel! This
is no time for sleeping!
55:
A resurgence of monsters in the
Farlands, that's what. They have
claimed many victims already.
60:
How bad are the casualties? What
are the Nine Houses doing?!
64:
C-calm down! Give me a moment,
and I'll explain!
68:
Sorry, I let my emotions get the
better of me...
72:
It's all right, I understand. The
memory of what happened five
years ago still burdens your heart...
76:
I learned the limits of what I could
do, and the lesson could not have
been more costly.
79:
But let's focus on the present. Tell
me the extent of the destruction and
what the nobles are doing to
combat it.
82:
It's already worse than five years
ago. The monsters are gaining
ground even in defended areas. As
for the nobles... they're fighting
amongst themselves.
84:
My brother Azrail... or rather, the
House of Swes is already taking
action, and I plan to go back to help.
88:
Azrail wants you to go there as well.
So... What do you say?
93:
I am all the Swallow Knights have
left. My resolve is the same as it has
always been.
96:
However, I am but one knight. What
help could I be?
103:
I'll take that to mean you're coming!
Perfect, let's not waste any more
time! I'm the one that will have to
hear from Azrail if anything goes
awry!
113:
First, we need to plan our
movements. Too many people
moving in a group would be
dangerous. I'm sorry, Alk, but...
117:
Sorry, Yuwel. I won't be able to come
with you this time.
122:
Don't worry. I know you're busy now
that the tower's complete. And if you
were to take part in this, it could
become a diplomatic issue.
126:
...If the need arises, I'll send for you,
but until then you can leave this to
us.
